summary: A good example of how unpredictable I find Killing Eve as a show is is this: When it was first speculated that Villanelle was...
body: A good example of how unpredictable I find Killing Eve as a show is is this: When it was first speculated that Villanelle was going to kidnap Konstatin’s daughter, I was nervous about it because I thought it was going to be a really dark part of the show and end with Villanelle murdering a child. But instead, Villanelle and Irina’s interactions ended up being some of the funniest scenes on the whole show.
